       SaRunLevelGet SaRunLevelIsSingleUser

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       These interfaces determine the run level of the local host
       system as defined by and reported by The system run  level
       is  important  for some applications that work differently
       in different states or may require the  services  provided
       by  a particular run level. The most useful distinction is
       likely to be between single  and  multi-user  run  levels.
       returns the run level as reported by "who(C) -r".  returns
       true (1) or false (0) depending on whether or not the sys-
       tem is in single user mode.

